WEBVTT

00:00:03.400 --> 00:00:06.360
In every professional setting, whether it's consulting, product

00:00:06.380 --> 00:00:09.900
development, nonprofits, or startups, you will work on teams.

00:00:10.370 --> 00:00:13.090
And the teams that deliver great work aren't the ones with the most

00:00:13.120 --> 00:00:14.120
talented people.

00:00:14.720 --> 00:00:17.150
They're the ones that figured out early how to work together.

00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:19.450
That's what this week is about.

00:00:19.700 --> 00:00:22.790
You're going to have conversations that feel small — how should

00:00:22.810 --> 00:00:25.420
we communicate, who does what, what happens when we

00:00:25.480 --> 00:00:26.100
disagree.

00:00:26.580 --> 00:00:29.630
But those conversations are what separate teams that function

00:00:29.700 --> 00:00:31.730
from teams that fall apart under pressure.

00:00:32.630 --> 00:00:35.620
You're also going to write your first professional message to a real

00:00:35.660 --> 00:00:39.330
employer contact. Not a professor, not a TA.

00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:43.060
Someone who will judge your team by how you come across.

00:00:43.570 --> 00:00:46.190
That's a skill you'll use in every job you ever have.

00:00:46.700 --> 00:00:48.090
None of this is theoretical.

00:00:48.530 --> 00:00:51.000
By the end of this week, you'll have a working team and a

00:00:51.050 --> 00:00:54.100
professional relationship underway. That's real.
